4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING PENALTIES FOR THE CRIME OF SEXUAL ASSAULT;
5 PROVIDING THAT OFFENDERS WHO COMMIT A SECOND OFFENSE OF SEXUAL ASSAULT MUST
6 REGISTER AS A SEXUAL OFFENDER; AND AMENDING SECTIONS 45-5-502 AND 46-23-502, MCA.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 Section 1. Section 45-5-502, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "45-5-502. Sexual assault. (1) A person who knowingly subjects another person to any sexual
12 contact without consent commits the offense of sexual assault.
13 (2) Except as provided in subsections (3) and (4):
14 (a) on a first conviction for sexual assault, the offender shall be fined an amount not to exceed
15 $500 $1,000 or be imprisoned in the county jail for a term not to exceed 6 months 1 year, or both;
16 (b) on a second conviction for sexual assault, the offender shall be fined an amount not to exceed
17 $1,000 $5,000 or be imprisoned in the county jail for a term not to exceed 1 year 5 years, or both; and
18 (c) on a third and subsequent conviction for sexual assault, the offender shall be fined an amount
19 not to exceed $10,000 or be imprisoned for a term not to exceed 5 10 years, or both.
20 (3) If the victim is less than 16 years old and the offender is 3 or more years older than the victim
21 or if the offender inflicts bodily injury upon anyone in the course of committing sexual assault, the offender shall
22 be punished by life imprisonment or by imprisonment in the state prison for a term of not less than 4 years,
23 unless the judge makes a written finding that there is good cause to impose a term of less than 4 years and
24 imposes a term of less than 4 years, or more than 100 years and may be fined not more than $50,000.
25 (4) If the victim is a client receiving psychotherapy services and the offender is providing or
26 purporting to provide psychotherapy services to the victim, the offender shall be punished by life imprisonment
27 or by imprisonment in the state prison for a term of not less than 4 years, unless the judge makes a written
28 finding that there is good cause to impose a term of less than 4 years and imposes a term of less than 4 years,
