21 this part, the following definitions apply:
22 (1) "Department" means the department of corrections provided for in 2-15-2301.
23 (2) "Foreign offenses" means a conviction for a sexual offense involving any of the conduct listed
24 in this section that was obtained under the laws of Canada, the United Kingdom, Australia, or New Zealand, or
25 under the laws of any foreign country when the United States department of state, in its country reports on
26 human rights practices, has concluded that an independent judiciary generally or vigorously enforced the right
27 to a fair trial in that country during the year in which the conviction was obtained.
28 (3) "Mental abnormality" means a congenital or acquired condition that affects the mental,
